I see the issue. Look at line 26-28 of the login page:

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (session.getToken()) router.replace(redirectTo);
}, [router, redirectTo]);
```

When the user lands on `/buyer/login?expired=1`, this effect checks for a token. If there's a stale token still in storage (the 401 interceptor clears it on non-auth pages but the user navigated directly), it redirects to `/buyer` — which then gets a 401, clears the token, and redirects back to `/buyer/login?expired=1` — creating a loop.

But wait — the interceptor at line 48 *does* call `session.clearToken()`. So by the time the user arrives at `/buyer/login?expired=1`, the token should already be cleared.

Let me check the toast component — the user says they "can't close the popup."

